SIMPLE: slut
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slut
<hw>Slut</hw> <pr>(sl⟦ucr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>slutte</ets>; cf. OD. <ets>slodde</ets> a slut, Icel.
<ets>sl⟦oum⟧ttr</ets> a heavy, loglike fellow, <ets>slota</ets> to
droop.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An untidy woman; a slattern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sluts</qex> are good enough to make a sloven's porridge.</q>
<rj><qau>Old Proverb.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A servant girl; a drudge.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our little girl Susan is a most admirable <qex>slut</qex>, and
pleases us mightily, doing more service than both the others.</q>
<rj><qau>Pepys.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A female dog; a bitch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slutch</ent>⟦br⟧
